<div id="banner">
	<h1>MediaCon: Lobbying</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<blockquote><p>Under heavy security, the agency&#8217;s normally docile monthly open meeting was disrupted twice by a dozen or so protesters who said they opposed plans by a majority on the FCC to ease ownership limits on the media industry.</p>

<p>&#8220;The further deregulation of the media is a blatant betrayal of the public interest,&#8221; said one protester. Another carried a pink tank top that read: &#8220;Mr. Powell, you&#8217;re fired.&#8221;</p>
</blockquote>
 - <a href="http://www.wired.com/news/technology/0,1282,58857,00.html">Wired News</a>

<p>Don&#8217;t see that kind of lobbying when they&#8217;re planning to <a href="http://boingboing.net/2003_05_01_archive.html#200291511">give more spectrum to WiFi</a> (&#8220;dammit, that&#8217;s our ox, where do you get off goring it?&#8221; available on pink tank-tops from Caf√© Press).</p>

